Key Match Events: Trent Alexander-Arnold scored a stunning free-kick into the top corner from 25 yards out
Declan Rice finished well as he burst into the six-yard box to get on the end of Ollie Watkins' low ball into the middle
Arttu Hoskonen headed home at the near post from a corner
Pre-Game Insights: Lee Carsley made six changes after England's shock defeat to Greece
Post-Match Reflections: England bounced back from their shock defeat to Greece with a 3-1 win over Finland
Goals from Jack Grealish, Alexander-Arnold and Declan Rice sent the visitors on their way to a much-needed win
Concerns at the back remain for England despite the win
Miscellaneous Highlights: England are worthy winners but Finland created openings and had half-chances to equalise
